OL,6,FThe government is under intense
OL,7,Fscrutiny about its management of the
OL,8,Feconomy.
OL,10,FMinisters point out that by increasing
OL,11,Fthe national minimum wage, freezing
OL,12,Fbus fares and making free school meals
OL,13,Fmore readily available, the government
OL,14,Fis "putting money in people's pockets"
OL,15,F- as it likes to say.
