OL,3,CUK inflation steady but food and drink
OL,4,Ccosts continue to climb
OL,6,FThe uncomfortable truth is that
OL,7,Finflation in the UK is much higher
OL,8,Fthan in either the Eurozone (2.1%) or
OL,9,Fthe US (2.9%) and that government
OL,10,Fpolicy has also put upward pressure on
OL,11,Fprices.
OL,13,FFood and drink inflation in the UK
OL,14,Frose for a fifth consecutive month and
OL,15,Fis running at 5.1%, materially higher
OL,16,Fthan the run rate of 1.5% before Covid.
