OL,3,CUK inflation steady but food and drink
OL,4,Ccosts continue to climb
OL,6,FThe weather ` there have been droughts
OL,7,Fin Brazil and poor harvests across
OL,8,FEurope ` has played a role, but
OL,9,Fsupermarkets and food producers say
OL,10,Fdecisions the Chancellor made in her
OL,11,FBudget last October have added 1`2% to
OL,12,Ffood prices across the board.
OL,14,FThe increases, in April, to the
OL,15,Fnational minimum wage and employer
OL,16,Fnational insurance contributions have
OL,17,Fsaddled businesses with higher costs `
OL,18,Fone way they have responded is by
OL,19,Fincreasing prices.
